(Home Router RX-500 - User Manual) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (1. Powering On the Router) Tj
T* (To turn on the router, plug the power adapter into the DC port.) Tj
T* (Press and hold the power button on the back for 2 seconds.) Tj
T* (The power LED turns solid green when the router is on.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (2. Resetting the Router to Factory Settings) Tj
T* (To reset the router, locate the small RESET pinhole on the back panel.) Tj
T* (Using a paperclip, press and hold the RESET button for 10 seconds.) Tj
T* (Release when all LEDs blink; the router restarts with default settings.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (3. Troubleshooting: No Internet Connection) Tj
T* (If the internet is down, first check that the WAN LED is solid green.) Tj
T* (Try rebooting the router: unplug it, wait 10 seconds, then plug it back in.) Tj
T* (If the problem persists, restart the router or contact support with your) Tj
T* (router serial number printed on the label underneath the device.) Tj
ET
